The paper proposes a novel generative data augmentation framework optimized for unsupervised anomaly detection using GANs. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also deals with computer vision tasks, which are covered by the cs.CV sub-category. The proposed method involves detecting anomalies, which is a security-related task, and hence, the paper may also belong to the cs.CR sub-category. Finally, the paper uses GANs, which are a type of neural network, and hence, the paper may also belong to the cs.NE sub-category.
